Weights recover well across all models. Loop parameters become increasingly uncertain for large values: when $\alpha$ is large, the Jardri function saturates, and further increases in $\alpha$ produce no additional behavioural signal. This asymptote limits precision at the upper tail but does not introduce bias for the moderate values expected in human participants.

